16/12/2010
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Montenegro took over the rotating six-month chairmanship of the Adriatic Charter from Macedonia on Wednesday (December 15th). 
Representatives of the US, Macedonia, Croatia, Albania, Montenegro and Bosnia and Herzegovina attended the ceremony in Skopje. 
A representative from Kosovo was on hand as an observer. 
The Adriatic Charter is a group of NATO aspirants formed in 2003 under a US initiative. 
Croatia and Albania joined the Alliance in 2009. 
